Class PCOR4

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • gui.PCOR4
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBoard, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible

    public class PCOR4
extends javax.swing.JPanel
implements IBoard
    Graphical representation of a PCOR4 board. This class inherits from JPanel, therefore it can be placed inside a window, such as a JFrame. In our application, it will be instantiated by the BoardsFrame class.
    According to the intracont reference manual, this board presents the following features:
    - Read Block (18 bytes): priority + flags + 8 2-byte input channels
    - Write Block (2 bytes): priority + flags
    Refer to the git repository for further details about how PROSAC handles them.
    Author:
    Gustavo CIOTTO PINTON
    See Also:
    IBoard, Serialized Form
